            review: "I found this class to be extremely challenging, but very rewarding. I took it my first semester in the OMS program, which was definitely a mistake! I'm coming from a non Computer Science (but still engineering) background, and I had almost no experience with C/C++. I ended up spending between 20-30 hours a week on the course lectures, readings, and assignments, and ended up with a 'B'. That being said, I learned a ton. Prof. Vuduc is an amazing professor, and I found the concepts fascinating. If you're not coming from a CS background, I would strongly recommend doing some prep work on C and parallel algorithms. And be prepared to spend a lot of time debugging and getting your code to run. In the end, I loved this class, but wish I had not taken it my first semester.",
